-- Fund manager Kames to stick with operating model after Scots vote - CIO
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Fri Sep 19, 2014 04:32AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 19 (Reuters) - Scottish fund manager Kames Capital, a unit of Dutch insurer Aegon <AEGN.AS>, has no plans to change the way it does business after Scotand rejected independence and faced the devolution of further powers from Westminster.

The firm was "content with the operating model we've always had", Chief Investment Officer Stephen Jones told Reuters.